notesStmt.note: Red ink extremely fugitive in water and often smeared across leaf or offset on next.
Signs of damp entry with a few tidemarks.
Losses to first few leaves and elsewhere have been infilled.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A daily prayer book according to the Italian rite.

msItem.title: A daily prayer book according to the Italian rite.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 20; written lines: 20; Uniform layout. Larger square initial words, partly highlighted in red ink. Hard-point ruling (complete) visible. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Captions of the drawings are perhaps in Judeo-Italian. Watermark of a fleur-de-lis, folio [183], unidentified.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Italian square and semi-cursive script of the 15th century, punctuated. Yisrael: the name Yisrael is decorated several times (e.g., folios 79v, 178v, 181v).

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Daily Prayers. Rite of N. Italy. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 11,924.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Purchased from Heinrich Eisemann by the British Museum on 27 October 1949: inscribed, folio [183v] (fse001v).
